    "The solution given by Zhao et al. (2021) and Holtzman et al. (2021) is calibration: adding compensation to the biased tokens so that they are calibrated to an unbiased status.",
    "Rhetorical situations can be used as a tool to achieve such calibrations.",
    "After Bitzer's piece (1968), several other scholars started analyzing the rhetorical situation.",
    "For Biesecker (1989), meaning is constructed by looking beyond binary constructions of speaker/situation, looking instead in the \"differencing zone\" (p. 118).",
    "She argued that while audience is an important element, we need to reconsider that the audience as unstable and shifting (p. 126), in other words-diverse and constantly changing."
